$ Oracle: Schedules
@ schedule

A *schedule* is a → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/scheduler/objects[scheduler object] which specifies when and how often a job is run.

A schedule is characterized by a
  • Start and end date, and an
  • repetition-interval

A schedule object is created with `dbms_scheduler.create_schedule`. After creating, it is automatically granted access to `PUBLIC`, so everyone can use a schedule.

sa:

 `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/scheduler/schedules`

  → development/databases/Oracle/objects
